== Entities ==
There are no documented entities in this level<ref>Some reports of Hounds inside caves have been made, but never confirmed.</ref>. All recorded fatalities are associated exclusively with environmental factors.

== Colonies and Outposts ==
Several groups have been formed for the exploration and documentation of the level, organizing themselves in rustic cabins or tents near small forests. Despite their differences, all groups operating within '''Level 626.2''' share an unspoken understanding: long-term habitation is possible only as long as one never begins to feel at home.

=== A.D.F. Alpine Research Post ===

* An advanced research outpost was created by the [[Another Dimension Foundation]] near the mountain slopes, being the only group to do so.
* Responsible for studying geological instability, unusual mineral formations, and high-altitude atmospheric conditions.
* Contains between 35 and 50 individuals, mostly geologists, anomaly analysts, structural engineers, and security agents.
* Most mountain missions are carried out using drones, fixed sensors, and motor probes, significantly reducing human risk.
* Generally has no conflicts with other groups, and limited, restricted exchanges occur with the '''Violet Mycology Camp'''.
* The outpost is not open to all wanderers, and unaffiliated wanderers are advised to remain in safe tents.

=== Violet Mycology Camp ===

* An organization hastily formed by [[M.E.G.]] members who fled during [[Level 626#M.E.G Outpost 626|The War of Level 626]] to this level.
* The first official group to settle at '''Level 626.2'''.
* Contains approximately 55 residents, all of whom are scientists and researchers.
* Dedicated to studying fungal adaptation to the soil’s toxic pH and the reproduction of purple clovers.
* Extremely neutral toward other groups and refuses any form of armed militarization.
* Always open to negotiation with anyone who contacts them.

=== Crossway Refuge ===

* An affiliated group of the [[Republic of Aurielle]] was created to provide psychological rest to wanderers who arrive here.
* The population varies greatly, usually ranging between 20 and 60.
* Located in a set of tents in front of forests and typically relocates every few weeks.
* Wanderers contacting '''Crossway Refuge''' should be aware that they offer psychological rest, not food.
* Despite being affiliated with the [[Republic of Aurielle]], they are not enemies of the '''Violet Mycology Camp''', as both reject militarization.
* Not a commercial organization and therefore does not usually engage in trade.

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===

* Touching the purple potted plant in the '''Purple Room''' at [[Level 314]] transports the subject to '''Level 626.2'''.
* At [[Level 626]], walking too far along a purple cloverfield path will lead here.
* Smelling purple flowers in The Hibiscus Valley<ref>Only in The Hibiscus Valley.</ref> at [[Level 83.1]] can make you fall asleep and wake up in this level.
* Rarely, when consuming '''Wrath''', you may faint at [[Level 660]] and wake up here.
* Following a purple cloverfield path behind the theater of [[Level 778|The Purple Hell]] .
* Finding any instance of living plant life in [[Level 393]] will eventually lead one here.

=== Exits ===

* Entering any salt cave at the base of '''The Cursed Mountains''' may lead to [[Level 620]].
* Walking by a forest nearby, spawning during a violet rain will lead to [[Level 626]].
